{"title_page": "24th Robert Awards", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Infobox film awards\n| number               = 24\n| award                = Robert Awards\n| award_link           = Robert Awards\n| image                = \n| caption              = \n| date                 = 2007<!-- {{Start date|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| site                 = \n| host                 = \n| producer             = \n| director             = \n| organizer            = [[Danish Film Academy]]\n| best_film            = \n| best_direction       = \n| best_direction_film  = \n| best_actor           = \n| best_actor_film      = \n| best_actress         = \n| best_actress_film    = \n| gold_award           = \n| hall_of_fame         = \n| most_wins            = \n| most_nominations     = \n| channel              = \n| network              = \n| duration             = \n| ratings              = \n| last                 = [[23rd Robert Awards|23rd]]\n| next                 = [[25th Robert Awards|25th]]\n}}\nThe '''24th [[Robert Awards]]''' ceremony was held in 2007 in [[Copenhagen]], Denmark. Organized by the [[Danish Film Academy]], the awards honoured the best in Danish and foreign film of 2006.\n\n== Honorees ==\n=== [[Robert Award for Best Danish Film|Best Danish Film]] ===\n* ''[[Dr\u00f8mmen]]'' \u2013 [[Niels Arden Oplev]]<ref name=\"Piil2008\">{{cite book |author=Morten Piil |authorlink=Morten Piil |title=Gyldendals danske filmguide |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=caRYl94i7xUC&pg=PT120 |year=2008 |publisher=Gyldendal A/S |location=Copenhagen, Denmark |language=Danish |isbn=978-87-02-06669-2 |pages=122\u2013}}</ref>\n\n=== [[Robert Award for Best Children's Film|Best Children's Film]] ===\n* ''[[Supervoksen]]'' \u2013 [[Christina Rosendahl]]\n\n=== [[Robert Award for Best Director|Best Director]] ===\n* [[Niels Arden Oplev]] \u2013 ''[[Dr\u00f8mmen]]''\n\n=== [[Robert Award for Best Screenplay|Best Screenplay]] ===\n* [[Niels Arden Oplev]] & Steen Bille \u2013 ''[[Dr\u00f8mmen]]''\n\n=== [[Robert Award for Best Actor in a Leading Role|Best Actor in a Leading Role]] ===\n* [[David Dencik]] \u2013 ''[[A Soap (film)|A Soap]]''\n\n=== [[Robert Award for Best Actress in a Leading Role|Best Actress in a Leading Role]] ===\n* [[Trine Dyrholm]] \u2013 ''[[A Soap (film)|A Soap]]''\n\n=== [[Robert Award for Best Actor in a Supporting Role|Best Actor in a Supporting Role]] ===\n* [[Bent Mejding]] \u2013 ''[[Dr\u00f8mmen]]''\n\n=== [[Robert Award for Best Actress in a Supporting Role|Best Actress in a Supporting Role]] ===\n* [[Stine Fischer Christensen]] \u2013 ''[[After the Wedding (2006 film)|After the Wedding]]''\n\n=== [[Robert Award for Best Cinematography|Best Cinematography]] ===\n* J\u00f8rgen Johansson \u2013 ''[[Prag (2006 film)|Prag]]''\n\n=== [[Robert Award for Best Production Design|Best Production Design]] ===\n* [[Peter De Neergaard]] \u2013 ''{{Interlanguage link multi|Der var en gang en dreng|da}}''\n\n=== [[Robert Award for Best Costume Design|Best Costume Design]] ===\n* [[Manon Rasmussen]] \u2013 ''[[Dr\u00f8mmen]]''\n\n=== [[Robert Award for Best Makeup|Best Makeup]] ===\n* Anne Katrine Sauerberg \u2013 ''[[A Soap (film)|A Soap]]''\n\n=== [[Robert Award for Best Special Effects|Best Special Effects]] ===\n* [[Thomas Dyg]] \u2013 ''[[The Lost Treasure of the Knights Templar]]''\n\n=== [[Robert Award for Best Sound Design|Best Sound Design]] ===\n* Hans M\u00f8ller \u2013 ''[[Prag (2006 film)|Prag]]''\n\n=== [[Robert Award for Best Editing|Best Editing]] ===\n* [[\u00c5sa Mossberg]] \u2013 ''[[Prag (2006 film)|Prag]]''\n\n=== [[Robert Award for Best Score|Best Score]] ===\n* {{Interlanguage link multi|Jeppe Kaas|da}} & [[Mikael Simpson]] \u2013 ''[[Rene hjerter]]''\n\n=== [[Robert Award for Best Song|Best Song]] ===\n* \"Jeg vil have en baby\" \u2013 ''{{Interlanguage link multi|Der var en gang en dreng|da}}''\n\n=== [[Robert Award for Best Non-American Film|Non-American Film]] ===\n* ''[[The Lives of Others]]'' \u2013 [[Florian Henckel von Donnersmarck]]\n\n=== [[Robert Award for Best American Film|Best American Film]] ===\n* ''[[Babel (film)|Babel]]'' \u2013 [[Alejandro Gonz\u00e1lez I\u00f1\u00e1rritu]]\n\n=== [[Robert Award for Best Short Fiction/Animation|Best Short Fiction/Animation]] ===\n* ''Partus'' \u2013 [[Mikkel Munch-Fals]]\n\n=== [[Robert Award for Best Long Fiction/Animation|Best Long Fiction/Animation]] ===\n* ''Liv'' \u2013 [[Heidi Maria Faisst]]\n\n=== [[Robert Award for Best Documentary Short|Best Documentary Short]] ===\n* ''Lyd p\u00e5 liv'' \u2013 Iben Haahr Andersen & [[Katia Forbert Petersen]]\n\n=== [[Robert Award for Best Documentary Feature|Best Documentary Feature]] ===\n* ''Menneskenes land'' - {{Interlanguage link multi|Anne Wivel|da}}\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal|Film|Denmark}}\n* [[60th Bodil Awards|2007 Bodil Awards]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official|http://filmakademiet.dk/robert-prisen/}} {{in lang|da}}\n\n{{Robert Awards}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Robert Awards, 24}}\n[[Category:2006 film awards]]\n[[Category:2007 in Denmark]]\n[[Category:Robert Awards ceremonies]]\n[[Category:2000s in Copenhagen]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Infobox film awards\n| number               = 24\n| award                = Robert Awards\n| award_link           = Robert Awards\n| image                = \n| caption              = \n| date                 = 2007<!-- {{Start date|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| site                 = \n| host                 = \n| producer             = \n| director             = \n| organizer            = [[Danish Film Academy]]\n| best_film            = \n| best_direction       = \n| best_direction_film  = \n| best_actor           = \n| best_actor_film      = \n| best_actress         = \n| best_actress_film    = \n| gold_award           = \n| hall_of_fame         = \n| most_wins            = \n| most_nominations     = \n| channel              = \n| network              = \n| duratio